Here’s a list of common computer peripherals and their functions, grouped by type
1. Input Devices

These are peripherals used to enter data and commands into the computer.

Peripheral	Function
Keyboard	                          Enters text, numbers, and commands
Mouse	                              Controls the pointer, selects and moves items on the screen
Scanner	                            Converts physical documents or images into digital form
Microphone	                        Captures audio input for recording or communication
Webcam	                            Captures live video input for calls or recording
Touchscreen	                       Allows users to interact directly with what’s on the screen
Game controller/joystick	      Inputs commands for gaming or simulations

2. Output Devices

These peripherals display or produce information from the computer.

Peripheral	Function
Monitor / Display	    Shows text, images, and videos
Printer	              Produces physical copies (hard copies) of documents or images
Speakers	            Output sound such as music or alerts
Headphones	          Provide private audio output
Projector	            Displays visual output on a larger surface for presentations

3. Storage Devices

Used to store or transfer data between computers.

Peripheral	Function
External Hard Drive / SSD	        Stores large amounts of data externally
USB Flash Drive	                  Portable storage for transferring files
Memory Card (SD Card)	            Stores data for cameras, phones, and computers
Optical Drive (CD/DVD/Blu-ray)	  Reads or writes data to discs (less common today)

4. Communication Devices

Used for networking and data transmission.

Peripheral	Function
Modem	                            Connects the computer to the internet through a phone or cable line
Network Interface Card (NIC)	    Allows wired or wireless network communication
Router	                          Connects multiple devices to a network or the internet
